                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.30/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-24T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1920—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. Navy Department has now designated a naval mission to proceed to Peru in
                    conformity with request of Peruvian Government.<note n="20" xml:id="d430fn20">In
                        accordance with Act of Congress, June 5, 1920 (41 Stat. 1056).</note> Head
                    of Mission is Commander Frank B. Freyer. Other members of mission in the order
                    of their rank are as follows: Commander Lewis D. Causey, former Commander
                    Charles G. Davy and former Lieutenant Paul Fitzsimons, the two latter being from
                    the resigned list. They are sailing by steamship <hi rend="italic">Santa
                        Elisa</hi> from New York August 25th. All except Causey are married and
                    accompanied by their wives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
